#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (<i lang=\"pli\">pācittiya</i>)"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs0.4"
msgid "Musāvādavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 7"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs0.5"
msgid "7. Dhammadesanāsikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on teaching"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs0.6"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.7.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.203"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa197"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā udāyī sāvatthiyaṃ kulūpako hoti, bahukāni "
"kulāni upasaṅkamati."
msgstr ""
"At that time Venerable Udāyī was associating with and visiting a number of "
"families in Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā udāyī pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena "
"aññataraṃ kulaṃ tenupasaṅkami."
msgstr ""
"One morning he robed up, took his bowl and robe, and went to a certain "
"family."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs1.4"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena gharaṇī nivesanadvāre nisinnā hoti, gharasuṇhā "
"āvasathadvāre nisinnā hoti."
msgstr ""
"Just then the housewife was sitting at the entrance door and the daughter-in-"
"law at the door to one of the rooms."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs1.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā udāyī yena gharaṇī tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā gharaṇiyā "
"upakaṇṇake dhammaṃ desesi."
msgstr ""
"Udāyī went up to the housewife and gave her a teaching, whispering in her "
"ear."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs1.6"
msgid "Atha kho gharasuṇhāya etadahosi—"
msgstr "And the daughter-in-law thought,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs1.7"
msgid "“kiṃ nu kho so samaṇo sassuyā jāro udāhu obhāsatī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is this ascetic my mother-in-law’s lover, or is he speaking lewdly?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.21"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa198"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs1.8"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā udāyī gharaṇiyā upakaṇṇake dhammaṃ desetvā yena gharasuṇhā "
"tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā gharasuṇhāya upakaṇṇake dhammaṃ desesi."
msgstr ""
"After teaching the housewife in this way, Udāyī approached the daughter-in-"
"law and gave her a teaching in the same way."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs1.9"
msgid "Atha kho gharaṇiyā etadahosi—"
msgstr "Then the housewife thought,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs1.10"
msgid "“kiṃ nu kho so samaṇo gharasuṇhāya jāro udāhu obhāsatī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is this ascetic my daughter-in-law’s lover, or is he speaking lewdly?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs1.11"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā udāyī gharasuṇhāya upakaṇṇake dhammaṃ desetvā pakkāmi."
msgstr "After giving a teaching in this way, Udāyī left."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs1.12"
msgid "Atha kho gharaṇī gharasuṇhaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "Then the housewife said to her daughter-in-law,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs1.13"
msgid "“he je, kiṃ te eso samaṇo avocā”ti?"
msgstr "“Hey, what did that ascetic say to you?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs1.14"
msgid "“Dhammaṃ me, ayye, desesi”."
msgstr "“He gave me a teaching, Madam."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs1.15"
msgid "“Ayyāya pana kiṃ avocā”ti?"
msgstr "But what did he say to you?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs1.16"
msgid "“Mayhampi dhammaṃ desesī”ti."
msgstr "“He gave me a teaching, too.”"

#. </p><p><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.204"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs1.17"
msgid "Tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "And they complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs1.18"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma ayyo udāyī upakaṇṇake dhammaṃ desessati."
msgstr "“How can Venerable Udāyī give teachings by whispering in the ear?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs1.19"
msgid "Nanu nāma vissaṭṭhena vivaṭena dhammo desetabbo”ti?"
msgstr "Should not teachings be given audibly and openly?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa199"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs1.20"
msgid ""
"Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tāsaṃ itthīnaṃ ujjhāyantīnaṃ khiyyantīnaṃ vipācentīnaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those women,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs1.21"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs1.22"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized Udāyī,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs1.23"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma āyasmā udāyī mātugāmassa dhammaṃ desessatī”ti."
msgstr "“How can Venerable Udāyī give teachings to women?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa200"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs1.24"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato "
"etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing him in many ways, they told the Master. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs1.25"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, udāyi, mātugāmassa dhammaṃ desesī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Udāyī, that you did this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs1.26"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs1.27"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs1.28"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, mātugāmassa dhammaṃ desessasi."
msgstr "“… Foolish man, how can you give teachings to women?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs1.29"
msgid "Netaṃ moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs1.30"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs1.30a"
msgid ""
msgstr "First preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa201"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs1.31"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu mātugāmassa dhammaṃ deseyya pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk gives a teaching to a woman, he commits an offense entailing "
"confession.’”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p class="endsection"><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa202"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs1.32"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.7.2"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.205"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa203"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena upāsikā bhikkhū passitvā etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr ""
"Soon afterwards some female lay followers saw some monks and said to them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs2.2"
msgid "“iṅghāyyā, dhammaṃ desethā”ti."
msgstr "“Venerables, please give a teaching.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs2.3"
msgid "“Na, bhaginī, kappati mātugāmassa dhammaṃ desetun”ti."
msgstr "“It’s not allowable for us to teach women.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs2.4"
msgid ""
"“Iṅghāyyā, chappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ desetha, sakkā ettakenapi dhammo "
"aññātun”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Please just teach five or six sentences. Even with that much it’s possible "
"to understand the Teaching.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs2.5"
msgid "“Na, bhaginī, kappati mātugāmassa dhammaṃ desetun”ti."
msgstr "“It’s not allowable for us to teach women.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs2.6"
msgid "Kukkuccāyantā na desesuṃ."
msgstr "And being afraid of wrongdoing, they did not teach them."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs2.7"
msgid "Upāsikā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "Then those female lay followers complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs2.8"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma, ayyā, amhehi yācīyamānā dhammaṃ na desessantī”ti."
msgstr "“How can they not teach us when asked?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa204"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs2.9"
msgid ""
"Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tāsaṃ upāsikānaṃ ujjhāyantīnaṃ khiyyantīnaṃ vipācentīnaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those female lay followers,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs2.10"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "and they told the Master."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs2.11"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā "
"bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards the Master gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs2.12"
msgid "“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, mātugāmassa chappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ desetuṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, I allow you to teach five or six sentences to a woman."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs2.13"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs2.13a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa205"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs2.14"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhū mātugāmassa uttarichappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ deseyya, "
"pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk gives a teaching of more than five or six sentences to a woman, "
"he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p class="endsection"><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.22"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa206"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs2.15"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Third sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.7.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa207"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs3.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū—“bhagavatā anuññātaṃ mātugāmassa "
"chappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ desetun”ti te aviññuṃ purisaviggahaṃ upanisīdāpetvā "
"mātugāmassa uttarichappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ desenti."
msgstr ""
"When the monks from the group of six knew that the Master had made this "
"allowance, they taught women more than five or six sentences in the presence "
"of a man who did not understand."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs3.2"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs3.3"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs3.4"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū aviññuṃ purisaviggahaṃ upanisīdāpetvā "
"mātugāmassa uttarichappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ desessantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“How can the monks from the group of six teach women more than five or six "
"sentences in the presence of a man who does not understand?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa208"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs3.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū chabbaggiye bhikkhū anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā "
"bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing those monks in many ways, they told the Master. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs3.6"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, aviññuṃ purisaviggahaṃ upanisīdāpetvā "
"mātugāmassa uttarichappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ desethā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs3.7"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs3.8"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs3.9"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, aviññuṃ purisaviggahaṃ upanisīdāpetvā "
"mātugāmassa uttarichappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ desessatha."
msgstr ""
"“… Foolish men, how can you teach women more than five or six sentences in "
"the presence of a man who doesn’t understand?"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.206"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs3.10"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs3.11"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs3.11a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
#. VAR: uttarichappañcavācāhi → uttariṃ ­chappañ­cavācāhi (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs3.12"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu mātugāmassa uttarichappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ deseyya, aññatra "
"viññunā purisaviggahena, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk gives a teaching of more than five or six sentences to a woman, "
"except in the presence of a man who understands, he commits an offense "
"entailing confession.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs3.13"
msgid "(<em>7</em>:<strong>56</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs3.13a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs3.14"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs3.15"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs3.16"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs3.17"
msgid "… pe … ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr ""
"…The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through "
"a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa211"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs3.18"
msgid "Mātugāmo nāma"
msgstr "A woman:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs3.19"
msgid "manussitthī; na yakkhī na petī na tiracchānagatā;"
msgstr ""
"a human female, not a female spirit, not a female ghost, not a female animal;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs3.20"
msgid "viññū, paṭibalā subhāsitadubbhāsitaṃ duṭṭhullāduṭṭhullaṃ ājānituṃ."
msgstr ""
"one who understands and is capable of discerning bad speech and good speech, "
"what is lewd and what is not lewd."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa212"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs3.21"
msgid "Uttarichappañcavācāhīti"
msgstr "More than five or six sentences:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs3.22"
msgid "atirekachappañcavācāhi."
msgstr "in excess of five or six sentences."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa213"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs3.23"
msgid "Dhammo nāma"
msgstr "A teaching:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs3.24"
msgid ""
"buddhabhāsito, sāvakabhāsito, isibhāsito, devatābhāsito, atthūpasañhito, "
"dhammūpasañhito."
msgstr ""
"what has been spoken by the Buddha, what has been spoken by disciples, what "
"has been spoken by sages, what has been spoken by gods, what is connected "
"with what is beneficial, what is connected with the Teaching."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa214"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs3.25"
msgid "Deseyyāti"
msgstr "Gives:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs3.26"
msgid "padena deseti, pade pade āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"if he teaches by the line, then for every line he commits an offense "
"entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs3.27"
msgid "Akkharāya deseti, akkharakkharāya āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If he teaches by the syllable, then for every syllable he commits an offense "
"entailing confession."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa215"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs3.28"
msgid "Aññatra viññunā purisaviggahenāti"
msgstr "Except in the presence of a man who understands:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
#. “Is present” is not actually found in the Pali, but it is implied.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs3.29"
msgid "ṭhapetvā viññuṃ purisaviggahaṃ."
msgstr "unless a man who understands is present."

#. </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs3.30"
msgid "Viññū nāma"
msgstr "A man who understands:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs3.31"
msgid ""
"purisaviggaho, paṭibalo hoti subhāsitadubbhāsitaṃ duṭṭhullāduṭṭhullaṃ "
"ājānituṃ."
msgstr ""
"one who is capable of discerning bad speech and good speech, what is lewd "
"and what is not lewd."

#. </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs4.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="20"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.7.4.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa216"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs4.2.1"
msgid ""
"Mātugāme mātugāmasaññī uttarichappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ deseti, aññatra viññunā "
"purisaviggahena, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is a woman, and he perceives her as a woman, and he teaches her more "
"than five or six sentences, except in the presence of a man who understands, "
"he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs4.2.2"
msgid ""
"Mātugāme vematiko uttarichappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ deseti, aññatra viññunā "
"purisaviggahena, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is a woman, but he is unsure if it is, and he teaches her more than "
"five or six sentences, except in the presence of a man who understands, he "
"commits an offense entailing confession."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.207"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs4.2.3"
msgid ""
"Mātugāme amātugāmasaññī uttarichappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ deseti, aññatra "
"viññunā purisaviggahena, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is a woman, but he does not perceive her as a woman, and he teaches "
"her more than five or six sentences, except in the presence of a man who "
"understands, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="21"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.23"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa217"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs4.2.4"
msgid ""
"Yakkhiyā vā petiyā vā paṇḍakassa vā tiracchānagatamanussaviggahitthiyā vā "
"uttarichappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ deseti, aññatra viññunā purisaviggahena, "
"āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he teaches more than five or six sentences to a female spirit, a female "
"ghost, a sexual nonconformist, or a female animal in the form of a woman, "
"except in the presence of a man who understands, he commits an offense of "
"wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs4.2.5"
msgid "Amātugāme mātugāmasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is not a woman, but he perceives it as a woman, he commits an offense "
"of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs4.2.6"
msgid "Amātugāme vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is not a woman, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong "
"conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs4.2.7"
msgid "Amātugāme amātugāmasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"If it is not a woman, and he does not perceive it as a woman, there is no "
"offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs4.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="22"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.7.4.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa218"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs4.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs4.3.2"
msgid "viññunā purisaviggahena,"
msgstr "if a man who understands is present;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs4.3.3"
msgid "chappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ deseti,"
msgstr "if he teaches five or six sentences;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs4.3.4"
msgid "ūnakachappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ deseti,"
msgstr "if he teaches less than five or six sentences;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs4.3.5"
msgid "uṭṭhahitvā puna nisīditvā deseti,"
msgstr "if he gets up and then sits down again and teaches;"

#. <i lang="pli">Tasmiṃ deseti</i>. According to <ref>Sp.4.751.8</ref> this locative should be read as a dative.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs4.3.6"
msgid "mātugāmo uṭṭhahitvā puna nisīdati tasmiṃ deseti,"
msgstr "if the woman gets up and then sits down again, and he then teaches her;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs4.3.7"
msgid "aññassa mātugāmassa deseti,"
msgstr "if he teaches another woman;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs4.3.8"
msgid "pañhaṃ pucchati,"
msgstr "if he asks a question;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs4.3.9"
msgid "pañhaṃ puṭṭho katheti,"
msgstr "if he is asked a question and then speaks;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs4.3.10"
msgid "aññassatthāya bhaṇantaṃ mātugāmo suṇāti,"
msgstr ""
"if he is speaking for the benefit of someone else and a woman listens in;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs4.3.11"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs4.3.12"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="23"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa219"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:pts-cs4.3.13"
msgid "Dhammadesanāsikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ sattamaṃ."
msgstr "The seventh rule, the training rule on teaching, is finished."

